{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/831","id":4117245640,"node_id":"PR_kwDOSbOoU871aC7I","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/831","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/831.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/831.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/831","number":831,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"fix(agentic): natural, command-free step narration for issue #819","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## What & why\n\nCloses the remaining items of #819. Merged PR #830 already fixed `find`\nrouting, the localized not-found message, and the report multiselect. This PR\naddresses the follow-up the user filed on the reported OpenCode session:\n\n> there is no need to print the command that will be executed in the message\n> before it, Formal AI just needs to explain what it is about to do, and command\n> anyway printed by OpenCode itself when actually executed.\n>\n> `so I can verify the next step before continuing.` does not produce any\n> meaningful information … it is not robotic but actually useful and natural.\n\n### Before (reported)\n\n```\nI'll use bash on find \"${FORMAL_AI_DESKTOP_DIR:-$HOME/Desktop}\" -type d \\( -iname 'hive*mind*control*center*' … so I can verify the next step before continuing.\n$ find \"${FORMAL_AI_DESKTOP_DIR:-$HOME/Desktop}\" -type d …\n```\n\n### After (matches how `claude` / `codex` phrase the same request)\n\n```\nLet me look on your Desktop for hive-mind-control center folder.\n```\n\nThe narration now never echoes the command — OpenCode prints it itself when the\nstep runs. Each capability gets a natural, spoken sentence in every supported\nlanguage (en/ru/hi/zh), the robotic tail is gone, and the empty-result and\nreport steps read plainly for a beginner.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`fix(agentic)`** — capability-aware, command-free narration selected from\n  the seed catalog (`tool_action_narration`); local path lookups get a\n  location-aware sentence built from the same extraction the `find` builder uses.\n- **`refactor(seed)`** — the natural `agentic_action_*` phrases live in a new\n  `data/seed/multilingual-responses-agentic.lino`, walked alongside the main\n  catalog via `RESPONSE_FILES`, keeping both under the 1,500-line seed guard.\n- **`test(agentic)`** — the whole OpenCode journey (find → empty result →\n  report → multiselect → combined action) is driven end to end through the real\n  HTTP API in `tests/integration/issue_819_report_flow.rs`, plus narration e2e\n  across the HTTP and typed-solver paths, and per-language narration pinned in\n  `tests/unit/issue_819_narration.rs` (en/ru/hi/zh).\n- **`docs(contributing)`** — recommends spawning a free `claude`/`codex`/\n  `opencode` model on the identical prompt to calibrate natural-language tone.\n\n## Self-hosting evidence\n\nThe user-facing fix is hand-authored maintenance, committed **without**\nself-authorship trailers per `CONTRIBUTING.md`. To keep the differential\nself-hosting ratchet honest on the branch, this PR also records a genuine piece\nof Formal-AI-authored release work under\n`docs/case-studies/issue-819/self-hosting-evidence/`: the system's own\nwhole-repository source-to-links projection (issue #558's \"translate the entire\nsource of our system to links and back\" recipe), driven through the real Agent\nCLI against a locally-served, memory-isolated Formal AI\n(`experiments/issue-819-self-hosting-evidence/run.sh`, session\n`ses_0702a074dffeiWQoNMe5nRv35f`).\n\nBoth recorded artifacts are deterministic, byte-for-byte reproducible functions\nof the embedded source tree (no neural inference):\n\n- `self-source-links.lino` / `session.json` — what the agentic loop recorded\n  through the Agent CLI (the responsive representative-slice projection).\n- `whole-repository-projection-NN.lino` — the exhaustive full-fidelity\n  projection: `SourceLinks::owned()` translating every one of the 292 owned\n  modules to Links Notation and back, each proven to round-trip byte-for-byte.\n  It is **sharded** into independently-valid Links Notation trees, each under\n  the 1,500-line `.lino` ceiling (`scripts/check-file-size.rs`), exactly as\n  `scripts/close-total.py` shards its generated closure. The new\n  `examples/project_source_links_sharded.rs` writes and asserts the shards.\n\nThe Agent CLI transcript (`agent-stream.jsonl`) and server trace\n(`formal-ai.log`) are the excluded evidence bundle binding the artifacts to the\nsession id.\n\n## How it was verified\n\n- Full suite: **2700 passed, 0 failed** (`cargo test --all`).\n- `cargo fmt --check` clean; `cargo clippy --examples --release -- -D warnings`\n  clean.\n- Self-hosting: trailer validation exit 0 (41.37 %, 2161/5224 changed lines);\n  `--check-ratchet origin/main` reports **\"self-hosting ratchet holds\"** (exit 0).\n- File-size guard, hardcoded-language guard, and changelog-fragment guard all\n  exit 0; every `.lino` shard is within the 1,500-line limit.\n- Language guards (`check:i18n`, `check:language-parity`,\n  `check:language-test-coverage`, `check:intent-coverage`) pass for en/ru/hi/zh.\n- Narration compared against `claude` and `codex` transcripts on the reported\n  prompt (see issue #819 screenshots) — the shipped phrasing matches their\n  natural, command-free shape.\n\n## Reproduce\n\n```bash\ncargo test --test integration issue_819_report_flow\ncargo test --test integration issue_819_narration\ncargo test --test unit issue_819_narration\n# Regenerate the sharded whole-repository projection (byte-for-byte stable):\ncargo run --release --example project_source_links_sharded -- \\\n  docs/case-studies/issue-819/self-hosting-evidence\n```\n\n\n\nFixes #819","created_at":"2026-07-23T14:09:33Z","updated_at":"2026-07-23T17:51:42Z","closed_at":"2026-07-23T17:51:42Z","merged_at":"2026-07-23T17:51:42Z","merge_commit_sha":"f6107035d0ae5873eccc343574574160ec356122","assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/831/commits","review_comments_url":"https://a